You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. There are commercial options to return to the UK from Uruguay. You should check availability with your travel agent but options include:
Iberia and Air Europa via Madrid
LATAM via Sao Paulo and Santiago
American Airlines via Miami
You should have your travel booked to your final destination before starting any journey, as you may not be allowed to board your flight without proof.
Travelling via Sao Paulo
Transit passengers cannot spend more than 24 hours in Sao Paulo. From Sao Paulo there are several flights to Europe.
Your journey home: re-entering the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy in Montevideo on +598 2622 3630.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
If you cannot leave Uruguay
If you cannot leave Uruguay at this time, see advice on staying in Uruguay during coronavirus.
